INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '57f94b3e-6a65-41f3-9224-b399b0cd27db',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Kafka MockConsumer — Testing Consumers Without a Running Broker$escape$,
  $escape$Testing Kafka consumers in isolation avoids broker overhead and keeps tests deterministic. The `kafka-clients` library ships a `MockConsumer<K, V>` that implements the full `Consumer<K, V>` interface — inject it instead of `KafkaConsumer` and control exactly what records your consumer sees.

Key setup: call `assign()` to bind partitions manually, seed offsets with `updateBeginningOffsets()`, then push records via `addRecord(new ConsumerRecord<>(topic, partition, offset, key, value))`. No ZooKeeper, no broker, sub-millisecond feedback.

For integration-level tests where real serialization, offset commits, and consumer group rebalancing matter, Spring Kafka's `@EmbeddedKafka` spins up an in-process broker on a random port. Annotate the test class with `@EmbeddedKafka(partitions = 1, topics = {"orders"})` and inject `EmbeddedKafkaBroker` to get the bootstrap address wired into your `KafkaTemplate` and listener containers.

Unit tests with `MockConsumer` catch deserialization bugs and business logic errors fast. Integration tests with `@EmbeddedKafka` catch offset management gaps and serialization round-trip failures. The two layers cover non-overlapping failure modes — run both.$escape$,
  $escape$val mockConsumer = MockConsumer<String, String>(OffsetResetStrategy.EARLIEST)
val partition = TopicPartition("orders", 0)
mockConsumer.assign(listOf(partition))
mockConsumer.updateBeginningOffsets(mapOf(partition to 0L))
mockConsumer.addRecord(
    ConsumerRecord("orders", 0, 0L, "k1", """{"id":1,"amount":99}""")
)

val orderService = mockk<OrderService>()
OrderConsumer(mockConsumer, orderService).pollOnce()

verify { orderService.process(match { it.id == 1 && it.amount == 99 }) }$escape$,
  $escape$kotlin$escape$,
